i  found the online platform to be a success for her students Learn more My online learning experience at UIC: Tyra Patterson UIC student Tyra describes her experience learning online Learn more First-year writing course increases belonging and retention Learn more UIC lecturer creates structure through online learning College of Liberal Arts and Sciences Lecturer Karen Leick made the most of the transition to online learning Learn more UIC Digital Humanities Initiative supports shift to e-learning Since classes were moved online, the initiative assisted faculty and instructors with the transition to the virtual classroom Learn more By having students work in their own homes and kitchens,  manager of the UIC Nutrition Garden Renea Lyles felt the new online learning reality was most applicable to students Learn more My online learning experience at UIC: Danielle Hull UIC student Danielle shares her tips for online learning Learn more Theatre class collaborates virtually to create ensemble project Students collaborated online to perfect their final spring performance Learn more Professor pivots to creative, online learning approach Professor Baker-Doyle quickly transitioned to online learning Learn more Missing the UIC campus? Visit virtually through Minecraft Kyle Chandetka, a third-year bioengineering student, has built part of the east side of campus for students who love UIC and Minecraft. Learn more Student Online Learning Resources Technology Solutions (formerly ACCC) Get the resources and support you need to succeed in an online learning environment Learn more University Library Search for resources online, download e-books, and make an appointment with a librarian Learn more Student troubleshooting tips Where to look if you’re having trouble with online resources Learn more Online assessment resources for students with disabilities Locate accessible UIC resources Learn more Collaboration tools From Blackboard to Zoom, find your favorite way to securely connect